From Hyberne , Scotland , eke from Fraunce ; Thyre prancyng horses tear the ground ; All strove to reche the place of fight , The first to exercise their might — O'Rocke upon his courser fleet , Who swift as lightning were his feet , First gained the lists and gat him fame ; From West Hybernee Isle he came , His might depictured in his name
that any of mortal men Could send so many to the grave

Sir John of the Dale or Compton hight , Advanced next in lists of fight , He knew the tricks of tourneying full well , In running race ne man
